  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN130.1-kilavi">kaḻaṟiya pāṅkaṟkut <app><lem>talaimakaṉ</lem><rdg wit="#C7">talaivaṉ</rdg></app> kaḻaṟṟetir <app><lem>maṟuttatu</lem><rdg wit="#NL #G1 #G2">colliyatu</rdg></app>.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How HE defended himself against the criticism of [his] scolding companion.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN130.1">
              <l>amma vāḻi kēḷir muṉṉiṉṟu</l>
              <l>kaṇṭaṉi rāyiṟ kaḻaṟalir maṉṉō</l>
              <l>nuṇṭātu potinta ceṅkāṟ koḻumukai</l>
              <l>muṇṭakaṅ keḻīiya mōṭṭumaṇa laṭaikaraip</l>
              <l>pē<supplied>e</supplied>yt talaiiya pi<supplied>ṇa</supplied>rarait tāḻai</l>
              <l>yeyiṟuṭai neṭu<supplied>n</supplied>tōṭu kāppap palavuṭaṉ</l>
              <l>vayiṟuṭaip pōtu vālitiṉ viraiip</l>
              <l>pulavuppo<supplied>ru</supplied> ta<supplied>ḻi</supplied>tta pūnāṟu pāyi</l>
              <l>ṉivartirai tanta vīrṅkatir muttaṅ</l>
              <l>kavarnaṭaip puravik kālvaṭut tapukku</l>
              <l>naṟṟēr vaḻuti koṟkai muṉṟuṟai</l>
              <l>vaṇṭuvāy tuṟanta vāṅkukaḻi neytaṟ</l>
              <l>pōtupuṟak koṭutta vuṇkaṇ</l>
              <l>mātar vāṇmuka mataiiya nōkkē.</l> 
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Alas, oh friends, if you had seen [it]</l>
                <l>standing in front [of you], you would surely not scold? (1f.)</l>
                <l>– the wanton look from a face with beautiful swords, (14)</l>
                <l>[her] kajal eyes that bring [to my mind] the outside of buds</l>
                <l>of blue waterlilies in the winding backwaters, abandoned by bee mouths (12f.)</l>
                <l>on the front ghat of Koṟkai, [belonging to] Vaḻuti with good chariots, (11)</l>
                <l>where the legs of the horses with expansive gait are hurt(?)</l>
                <l>by pearls with moist rays brought by the waves climbing</l>
                <l>the expanse fragrant with flowers that competed with [and] overcame</l>
                <l>the stench of fish, purely exuding perfume from bellied buds, (7-10)</l>
                <l>many together, while the toothed long leaves of the Tāḻai</l>
                <l>with rough trunks that offer [a likeness with?] demonesses protect [them], (5f.)</l>
                <l>on the settling shore with high sands joined by Muṇṭakam shrubs</l>
                <l>with red-stemmed rich buds that have hoarded fine pollen. (3f.)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
